				\begin{document}$$\mathrm{Mortality rate} =\frac{\mathrm{No}.\mathrm{ of death cases from a specific time}*100}{\mathrm{Total No}.\mathrm{ of death in the population}}.$$\end{document}Mortalityrate=No.ofdeathcasesfromaspecifictime∗100TotalNo.ofdeathinthepopulation.
